name: King of Stonks
overview: Felix Armand wants to be at the top. Because once he's there, he can finally be a decent human being. After all, he's the damn mastermind behind the most successful FinTech company of all time, and all of Germany: the CableCash AG. Unfortunately, everything is already blowing up in Felix's face during the IPO: Money laundering, investor deception, internet pornography. As a medium-sized company, you certainly don't get applauded for using such methods by the German public.

episodes.name: It's the Economy, Stupid
episodes.overview: On the day of a crucial presentation, Felix discovers a pornographic scandal tied to CableCash — and stumbles across a seductive con-artist.

episodes.name: Do's and Don'ts
episodes.overview: Felix lands in hot water with the Sicilian Mafia after vengeful investors expose the mob's relationship with CableCash.

episodes.name: Cramer Bounce
episodes.overview: At a summit for FinTech big players, Felix must pick up the pieces after Magnus leaves the company hanging. Sheila teams up with a spiteful journalist.

episodes.name: Midnight Express
episodes.overview: Fed up with Magnus’ instability, Felix considers an unlikely alliance to restore order as CableCash's surprising growth creates public suspicion.

episodes.name: Master of Bullsh*t and A**holery
episodes.overview: Sheila’s flirtation with Felix heats up — along with her plans against CableCash. Meanwhile, a sudden resignation leads to a shocking discovery.

episodes.name: Panic
episodes.overview: After uncovering her secret, Felix confronts Sheila about her intentions while CableCash’s true identity comes to the surface.
